Hey, I've been in show business
a long time, Huey.

17:09.000 --> 17:12.000
This kind of thing comes
with the territory.

17:12.000 --> 17:14.000
I know you'll do
the right thing.

17:21.000 --> 17:23.000
UBERWITZ:
Huey, it could still be

17:21.000 --> 17:23.000
a great play.

17:23.000 --> 17:26.000
We could cut a few scenes.
Make some changes to the script.

17:26.000 --> 17:27.000
Huey.

17:27.000 --> 17:30.000
We have
to put something on.

17:31.000 --> 17:32.000
Do what you have to do.

17:33.000 --> 17:35.000
Just take my name off of it.

17:35.000 --> 17:37.000
Won't be my vision.

17:41.000 --> 17:43.000
Hello.

17:43.000 --> 17:46.000
Yeah. Yeah, it's resolved.

17:46.000 --> 17:49.000
We'll be ready to put
the play on tomorrow.

17:50.000 --> 17:53.000
Why doesn't
the real Santa come?

17:53.000 --> 17:56.000
'Cause there ain't
no real Santa.

18:00.000 --> 18:02.000
HUEY: We all want to believe

18:00.000 --> 18:02.000
in miracles on Christmas.

18:12.000 --> 18:13.000
All of us.

18:19.000 --> 18:23.000
RUCKUS:
No Santa Claus?

18:23.000 --> 18:26.000
Well, I'd expect
a heathen nigglet like Riley

18:27.000 --> 18:28.000
to say something like that.

18:28.000 --> 18:31.000
But, Jazmine,
I'm surprised at you.

18:31.000 --> 18:33.000
Being a mulatto and all,

18:33.000 --> 18:36.000
you've supposed
to have more sense.

18:36.000 --> 18:37.000
Huh?

18:37.000 --> 18:39.000
I'm Special Agent Ruckus.

18:39.000 --> 18:40.000
Shh!

18:40.000 --> 18:43.000
Volunteer Santa Security.

18:44.000 --> 18:46.000
Santa has reason to believe

18:46.000 --> 18:48.000
that your little
jungle friend Riley

18:48.000 --> 18:51.000
may be the Santa Stalker.

18:51.000 --> 18:55.000
That makes perfect sense.

18:55.000 --> 18:57.000
Mm-hm. Santa couldn't
come this year.

18:57.000 --> 18:59.000
Just wasn't safe.

18:59.000 --> 19:01.000
Maybe next year.

19:01.000 --> 19:05.000
So...he's real?

19:05.000 --> 19:09.000
Real as the Irish blood
charging through my veins.

19:09.000 --> 19:11.000
HUEY: But Christmas miracles

19:09.000 --> 19:11.000
only happen

19:12.000 --> 19:14.000
in the lies adults tell to children.

19:16.000 --> 19:19.000
And maybe in Christmas specials.

19:20.000 --> 19:23.000
Mr. Uberwitz put on the play as scheduled.

19:23.000 --> 19:25.000
Not a single word was changed.

19:39.000 --> 19:41.000
And so, by some miracle,

19:41.000 --> 19:44.000
the world saw my vision that night.

19:44.000 --> 19:45.000
The Adventures of Black Jesus

19:45.000 --> 19:48.000
received a 20-minute standing ovation.

19:48.000 --> 19:51.000
It was called "a stunning revolution in theatre"

19:51.000 --> 19:52.000
by the  Woodcrest Post Gazette.

19:53.000 --> 19:57.000
Unfortunately, the PTA protest had gained some ground.

19:57.000 --> 20:00.000
Seems that people didn't care about my vision.

20:00.000 --> 20:03.000
They cared about seeing their kids on stage.

20:03.000 --> 20:04.000
Who knew?

20:04.000 --> 20:06.000
JAZMINE:
Yay, Huey!

20:06.000 --> 20:08.000
Yay!

20:10.000 --> 20:13.000
Mr. Uberwitz was fired for disobeying orders

20:14.000 --> 20:16.000
and for generally being an irresponsible white person.

